<LEADPARA>  Cable television king Ted Turner certainly seems to get restless a lot. After
conquering the yachting and TV news worlds -- and capturing Jane Fonda's fancy
along the way -- terrible Ted says he wants to "hit the big one, one more
time.";   And just what hostile horizon is he talking about? Well, bison.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Front  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  HOME ON TED'S RANGE  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  People  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Seems he wants to turn his 130,000-acre Montana ranch into his next big
venture. "I want to have the biggest buffalo-breeding ranch in the country and
have a ball doing it," he said. He envisions a future where he'll sell the
bulls for meat and the cows to other breeders. Eventually he hopes buffalo rib
roasts will be Sunday suppers across the country.;   "I want to show you can
do something in balance with nature and still make money doing it, twice as
much money as you could with cattle," said the owner of 2,000 head of bison.
Turner's beef with cattle is their expensive, involved upkeep. "But with
buffalo," he opines, "it's a whole different ballgame." Listen to the owner of
baseball's Braves. He ought to know.  </TEXT>
